data.title: MSHSL Section 1AA Softball Tournament Pairings
data.meta_description: Class 2A top rated Randolph was awarded the #1 seeding in the Section 1AA Softball Tournament which opens Monday, May 20, 2024. The undefeated Rockets get a bye.
data.text:
Class 2A top rated Randolph was awarded the #1 seeding in the Section 1AA Softball Tournament which opens Monday, May 20, 2024. The Rockets get a bye and will host either #8 Cannon Falls (10-8) or #9 Pine Island (8-8).

Randolph enters the playoffs with a 20-0 record. #2 seed Caledonia (18-2) dropped their season opener 6-5 to Cotter and fell 2-1 to Class 3A Stewartville.. The Warriors entertain #15 seed Lake City (2-16) on Monday, May 20, 2024.

#3 seed Dover-Eyota (14-6) has #14 Triton (3-16) come to Eagles country with #6 Chatfield (13-7) hosting #11 Rochester Lourdes (7-12).

#4 seed Zumbrota-Mazeppa (8-10) tangles with #13 Grand Meadow-Leroy-Ostrander-Kingsland (7-10) while #5 Cotter (14-6) hosts #12 Plainview-Elgin-Millville (4-16)

Randolph enters playoff action with a team batting average of ,357 with 193 hits including 78 extra base hits. The Rockets have scored 162 runs and only committed 12 errors all season.

Carter Raymond, junior, pitcher has thrown all 126 innings with 38 hits allowed, 8 runs, 7 earned with 5 walks and 231 strikeouts, 53 looking. Raymond has hit 6 batters with pitches. She has a o.389 ERA.

Randolph has allowed 8 stolen bases in 14 attempts. Opponents have a .091 batting average against Raymond.
